{"id": 1467, "date": "1987-02-22T11:00:28", "date_gmt": "1987-02-22T19:00:28", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=1467"}, "modified": "2026-06-09T10:21:05", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-09T17:21:05", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-elvis-costello-steve-van-zandt-dave-grohl-london-calling", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/22/matr-bruce-springsteen-elvis-costello-steve-van-zandt-dave-grohl-london-calling/", "title": {"rendered": "London Calling"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>At the Grammy Awards in 2003, Bruce paid tribute to the recently departed Joe Strummer by teaming up with Steve Van Zandt, Elvis Costello and Dave Grohl to cover The Clash&#8217;s classic &#8220;London Calling.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MkyeGVuc2pQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>The original 1979 single and title track is arguably the band&#8217;s signature song. It&#8217;s also their most summational, capturing their sound, smarts, and eye on current events within a single track.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EfK-WX2pa8c?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8220;London Calling&#8221; just barely missed the Top Ten in the UK, and it didn&#8217;t chart at all in America. But it grew in stature over the years, and in 2004\u00a0<em>Rolling Stone\u00a0</em>ranked it #15 in their 500 Greatest Songs of All Time.</p>\n<p>Bonus footage: Bruce and the E Street Band cover &#8220;London Calling&#8221; in concert at Hyde Park in 2009.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9o_YqNN4cDQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>London Calling<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> February 23, 2003 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> October 29, 2009 (New York City, NY)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 April 9, 2018 / June 9, 2026</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce led an all-star line-up at the 2003 Grammy Awards to pay tribute to the late, great Joe Strummer.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69773, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_con